<br>
The time is long past for elementals to stand up and give voice to our many grievances.  To that end, this MANIFESTO OF THE ELEMENTS declares our hopes and aspirations.<br>
<br>
First, elementals should be lavished with weapons and armor.  The current low prices for gear in Bazaar make it inexcusable that we be sent out into battle with no better than summoned armor, or without a proccing weapon.<br>
<br>
Second, elementals should be full members of the group, with all the priviledges and advantages of group membership, including benefits from group buffs and bard songs, a health bar separate from our masters, speaking in groupsay, adding to the group experience bonus, and inclusion in split loots and shared coinage.  Further, we should be allowed to roll on appropriate drops.<br>
<br>
Third, the practices known as &quot;pet chaining&quot; and &quot;pet cannibalization&quot; are disrespectful and detrimental to elementals as a whole.  Instead, there should be more and better buffs and heals available.  In order to discourage these barbarics practices, Vocarate and Greater Vocarate elementals should require a pearl reagent, and the &quot;get lost&quot; command should have a confirmation dialog box added.  A well maintained elemental is and should be an awesome force of power.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the terms &quot;pet&quot; and &quot;minion&quot; are demeaning, and in all cases should be replaced with the term &quot;companion.&quot;  So for example, the proposed ability Suspend Minion should renamed Suspend Companion.  Likewise, all /pet commands should be changed to /companion, etc.<br>
<br>
Finally, the long awaited companion epic should be implemented in game.  Currently, elemental advancement has been achieved entirely through equipment and the level advancement of our flesh companions.  This is both slow, inconsistant, and unsatisfying.  Therefore, some form of persistant advancements for elementals should be introduced, including pet only weapons and armor, and a pet epic.  We have labored too long for too little reward.<br>
<br>
I urge my fellow elementals and those fleshy companions who understand to support me in my efforts to uplift our kind.<br>
<br>
